<p>In my application I have celery task that make subprocess call to external bin (may be not installed). </p>  <p>My task acts as follow:</p>  <pre><code>class MyTask(app.Task):      def __init__(self):        try:            do_some_check_on_the_ext_bin()        except (subprocess.CalledProcessError, subprocess.TimeoutExpired):             raise EnvironmentError     def run(self, **kw):        do_the_job_and_call_the_bin() </code></pre>  <p>But I wonder if it the best way to do, to put the environment check in the init method ? </p>